==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Secessionist
<hw>Se*ces"sion*ist</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who upholds
secession.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(U.S. Hist.)</fld> <def>One who holds to the belief
that a State has the right to separate from the Union at its
will.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Seche</ent>⟦br⟧
